Robert Jordan: The Wheel of Time (1990-2013)
- protagonists: Rand al'Thor/Lews Therin Telamon + Elayne + Aviendha + Min, Mat Cauthon + Tuon/Daughter of Nine Moons, Perrin Aybara + Faile/Zarine, Egwene al'Vere, Nynaeve al'Meara
- antagonists: Padan Fain, Shadowspawn (Trollocs, Myrddraal, Draghkar), Forsaken (Ishamael/Moridin, Lanfear/Cyndane, Balthamel + Aginor, Asmodean, Demandred, Be'lal, Rahvin, Sammael, Moghedien, Semirhage, Mesaana, Graendal, Mazrim Taim), Whitecloaks, Seanchan (High Lady Suroth), Shaido, Black Ajah (Liandrin)
- other: Andor (Morgase, Gawyn + Galad), Aes Sedai (Amyrlin Seat, Moiraine + Lan, Siuan, Elaida), Asha'man (Logain), ogier Loial, Aiel (Maidens of Spear, Wise Ones), Tuatha'an
- places: Andor (Two Rivers, Caemlyn), Tar Valon, Cairhien, Tear, Illian, Altara, Amadicia, Tarabon, Arad Doman, Tel'aran'rhiod
- The Eye of the World: journey from Two Rivers to Caemlyn, travel via Ways and battle in Shienar
- The Great Hunt: pursue of Horn from Shienar to Toman Head, battle against Seanchan
- The Dragon Reborn: journey to Tear, Rand kills Ba'alzamon with sword Callandor, Moiraine kills Be'lal, Aiel conquer Tear
- The Shadow Rising: journey to Aiel Waste, Rand becomes Car'a'carn in Rhuidean, Perrin saves Two Rivers, Elaida overthrows Siuan as Amyrlin
- The Fires of Heaven: Rand + Mat + Aiel defeat Shaido in Cairhien, Moiraine sacrifices to stop Lanfear, Rand kills Rahvin, Nynaeve captures Moghedien
- Lord of Chaos: Egwene becomes Amyrlin of rebels in Salidar, Aes Sedai capture Rand and Perrin + Aiel + Asha'man rescue him
- A Crown of Swords: Rand kills Sammael and conquers Illian, Seanchan conquer Ebou Dar
- The Path of Daggers: battle against Seanchan in Ebou Dar
- Winter's Heart: Rand and Nynaeve cleanse Saidin
- Crossroads of Twilight: nothing
- Knife of Dreams: Mat marries Seanchan empress, Elayne becomes Andor queen
